returns.r: The result as an uint256. Result must have at most 256 bit.

divRem512x256(uint256,uint256,uint256,ui.notice: Calculates the division of a 512 bit unsigned integer by a 256 bit integer. It  requires the remainder to be known and the result must fit in a 256 bit integer.

params.a0: A uint256 representing the low bits of the nominator.
params.a1: A uint256 representing the high bits of the nominator.
params.rem: A uint256 representing the remainder of the devision. The algorithm is cheaper to compute if the remainder is known. The remainder often be retreived cheaply using the mulmod and addmod operations.

returns.r: The result as an uint256. Result must have at most 256 bit.
